<definition-item date-revised="2022-08-01"><classification-symbol scheme="cpc">A47D1/008</classification-symbol><definition-title>{with trays  (children&apos;s chairs combined with tables <class-ref scheme="cpc">A47D3/00</class-ref>)}</definition-title><definition-statement><section-title>Definition statement</section-title><section-body><paragraph-text type="preamble">This place covers:</paragraph-text><paragraph-text type="body">Subject matter including a chair and an attached tray. The tray is an element having a horizontal surface (at least in an operative or use position) configured to support articles on top of it. In general, the tray is relatively small (a table encircling a chair is not considered a tray; see the references below) so that the supporting structure of the chair and tray is not substantially larger than required to support a chair alone. The tray is attached to only a single chair.</paragraph-text></section-body></definition-statement><references><section-title>References</section-title><limiting-references><section-title>Limiting references</section-title><section-body><paragraph-text type="preamble">This place does not cover:</paragraph-text><table>
